# Cursor AI Rules for terraform-provider-rundeck

Please read and follow all instructions from `.github/copilot-instructions.md`.

That file contains comprehensive guidelines for:
- Architecture and critical patterns
- Testing requirements (including Enterprise feature flags)
- Common pitfalls and field mapping issues
- Code style requirements
- Documentation standards
- PR review checklist
- Always use `make fmt` before commits to ensure CI/CD will pass.

When working on this codebase, reference those instructions for detailed guidance.

## Critical Reminder — Terraform Registry Publishing

If the Registry rejects a provider version with "duplicated key not allowed" or `ConflictError`, check for **duplicate documentation files** in `website/docs/` BEFORE investigating schema or code. Two files with the same base name but different extensions (`.md` vs `.markdown`) in the same subdirectory will cause this error for every version until removed.

